{
  "files": [],
  "references": [
    { "path": "./tsconfig.app.json" },
    { "path": "./tsconfig.node.json" }
  ]
}

// | Key          | Value                                                                 | What It Does                   | Why It’s Used                    |
// | ------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------ | -------------------------------- |
// | `files`      | `[]`                                                                  | No files are directly included | Uses project references instead  |
// | `references` | `[{ path: "./tsconfig.app.json" }, { path: "./tsconfig.node.json" }]` | Links multiple TS configs      | Enables multi-project setup      |
// | `path`       | `./tsconfig.app.json`                                                 | Refers to frontend TS config   | Type-checks React/Vite app       |
// | `path`       | `./tsconfig.node.json`                                                | Refers to Node TS config       | Type-checks Vite config, scripts |


// Big Picture (Very Important)
// tsconfig.json   (root / orchestrator)
//    ├── tsconfig.app.json   (frontend / React)
//    └── tsconfig.node.json  (Node / tooling)


// ✔️ Clean separation
// ✔️ Faster builds
// ✔️ Better scalability